Chippa United striker Augustine Kwem said the signing of Cameroonian Bienvenu Eva Nga has created competitive spirit in the team. Kwem had a successful debut season in the PSL, netting eight goals across all competitions. The 23-year-old striker joined the Chilli Boys from ABC Motsepe League side Sibanye FC on a one-year deal in July 2019. Read the full story at HeraldLIVE